<h2 id="110">4. Activating payment methods</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For PAYONE, a large variety of payment methods is available. Go to <strong><a href="/en/order-processing/payment/managing-payment-methods#20">Settings » Orders » Payment » Payment methods</a></strong> to activate the payment methods.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="115">5. Displaying PAYONE in the online store</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>CMS</strong> menu, you can customise the text that is displayed during the order process when customers select the payment method PAYONE. In addition, you will find out where to customise the design by modifying the CSS. You can customise the forms for credit card data and online bank transfers. For further information, refer to the <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/cms#web-design-editing-the-web-design-order-process-checkout"><strong>Checkout</strong></a> page.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Customising the online forms:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » Web design</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the folder <strong>Order process » Checkout</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand a <strong>PAYONE payment method</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a text into the <strong>Text in front of</strong> or <strong>Text behind</strong> field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can also customise the order confirmation form. For further information, refer to the <strong><a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/cms#web-design-editing-the-web-design-order-process-order-confirmation">Order confirmation</a></strong> page.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Customising the order confirmation:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » Web design</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the folder <strong>Order process » Order confirmation</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand a <strong>PAYONE payment method</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a text into the <strong>Text in front of</strong> or <strong>Text behind</strong> field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can find the CSS for the PAYONE payment methods in the <strong>CMS » Web design » Layout » CSS » CSSOrder</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
